<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE - OIL
        PUMP
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OIL PUMP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the Allen-head bolts and washers that fasten the pump to the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303372">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303372" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303372.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Remove Bolts and Washers Fastening Pump to Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bracket for the pick-up tube from the case.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pump. If necessary, hit the pump with a plastic or rubber hammer to separate the
                pump from the case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the pick-up screen on the tube. If the tube or screen is damaged, replace the pick-up
                tube assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If used, inspect the pump-to-case O-ring on the front of the pump. If worn or damaged,
                replace the O-ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cover and inspect the pump. Replace the O-ring if worn or damaged. Replace the
                pump if the rotors are worn or damaged
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303373">(Figure 73).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303373" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303373.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 73. Replace Pump if Rotors are Worn or Damaged</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
